We recently found out about @saintcloudbourbon, a high end bourbon crafted by a wine maker, and we can't wait to try it! You've got to have some serious skill to mix with top shelf spirits, but check out @bad_birdy making it look easy (as she always does)! 💯 Here's what she had to say, "Saint Cloud is a beautifully crafted by Ray Walker who I have the pleasure to call my friend. His experience in wine making has truly set the stage for the success of his exceptional whiskey."
“Saint & Sinner”
▪️2oz Saint Cloud Bourbon
▪️.75oz Italian Sweet Vermouth 
▪️.5oz Biscotti Liqueur 
▪️Bar-spoon of Salted Caramel Syrup 
▪️4 dashes of Fig & Fennel Bitters
Glass: Double Old Fashioned
Garnish: Painted Edible 24k Gold (What!?), Cherry & Orange Peel

From the LTD barstool at @nobleexperiment 💯 This is place where it all started…the first craft cocktail experience we ever had 10 years ago and the reason we were immediately hooked! I love the fact that now there’s zero menus - it’s all bartender’s choice based on what you enjoy drinking. When I let @keylathelion do her thing and the cocktail involves @delmagueymezcal and @campariofficial - I know I’m home… 🙏

Can’t wait to do a real LTD shoot at @nobleexperiment 🙌

By the way…that freezer cam was 🔥 🙌

.75oz lemon

1oz Aperol 
2 dashes of firewater bitters

Get involved with #beeskneesweek this year! Whether you make cocktails at home or you’re a professional bartender, being a part of #BeesKneesWeek is a clear and easy way to do some good in the world. For every Bee’s Knees Cocktail made and shared online, @barrhillgin will plant 10 sq/ft of bee habitat. It’s really that simple. Link in bio for more info or click here:
www.beeskneesweek.com

@cocktailsbyhawk is one of three bartenders we took to @thevalleyhive for an immersive experience with the bees, which inspired his #beeskneesweek contribution.
“After getting a sample of the fresh wildflower honey we collected at @thevalleyhive, I was determined to make sure that flavor stood out in the cocktail, so I decided to go with a drink that wouldn’t require citrus, hence the Old Fashioned. I knew @barrhillgin’s barrel-aged Tom Cat Gin would be a perfect fit. I also managed to find two bitters in my collection that would compliment both the gin and the honey.”

Dang!
2 oz Barr Hill Tom Cat Gin
2 teardrop bar spoon dips of The Valley Hive Wildflower Honey 🍯 
2 dashes cherry clove vanilla bitters
2 dashes fig orange bitters
Garnish with honey wand, orange peel, and edible flower
🧊: @pennypoundice
🎥: @86.thebartender for Licensed To Distill™️

#bee #beekeeping #bar #bartending #bartender #honey #honeycomb #savethebees #cocktail #gin

Our friends at @volcantequila & @middletonmixology crafted a very exclusive Volcan version of the SmokeTop🔥 We were at @tocamadera when @charitykjohnston created the first cocktail using the new SmokeTop and as you can see it is visually stunning! 💯 Volcan Tequila harvests their agave in the shadow of a volcano and now your cocktail can be smoked in the shadow of a volcano as well…🌋🍹
(Drink Recipe Below)

🎥: Shot and edited by @aj_sjostrom for Licensed To Distill®
📸: Cover photo by @spiritandspoon 

“De la Tierra” by @charitykjohnston
2oz @volcantequila Cristalino
1oz epazote, bell pepper & mango purée 
1oz lemon 
.5oz Campari 
.5oz Amaro

This gorgeous cocktail from @laws.and.liquids is one of the first entires in this month’s @homebarawards challenge. 🏆 @homebarawards has joined us this month for @barrhillgin’s #beeskneesweek by making the Bee's Knees Cocktail their official challenge of the month! If you participate in #beeskneesweek, and in the Home Bar Awards challenge, that means that not only are you making sure another 10 sq/ft of bee habitat are planted just by posting, but you're also in the running to win some sweet LTD swag, some sweet @barrhillgin swag, and we'll be reposting the winning cocktail right here jn our channel too! 💯 Head over to @homebarawards for more details and get involved. 👍

Here’s more details on the cocktail:
“The classic Bee's Knees is gin, honey and lemon juice. I wanted to use apple because it's seasonal and complements the Barr Hill. So I acid-adjusted fresh apple cider to give it the tartness of lemon-lime juice. Then I infused honey syrup with ginger and cinnamon for flavors that evoke autumn and pair well with honey, juniper and apple. I shook the drink with egg white for texture and aesthetics. Then I misted it with Creole bitters for color and aromas of anise, pepper and wood. 

Recipe:
2 oz @barrhillgin
1 oz acid-adjusted fresh apple cider*
1 oz ginger & cinnamon-infused honey syrup**
Egg white
@thebittertruthcompany Creole bitters sprayed on top

#homebar #homebarawards #beeskneesweek #gin #savethebees #bees

We recently found out about @saintcloudbourbon, a high end bourbon crafted by a wine maker, and we can't wait to try it! You've got to have some serious skill to mix with top shelf spirits, but check out @bad_birdy making it look easy (as she always does)! 💯 Here's what she had to say, "Saint Cloud is a beautifully crafted by Ray Walker who I have the pleasure to call my friend. His experience in wine making has truly set the stage for the success of his exceptional whiskey."
“Saint & Sinner”
▪️2oz Saint Cloud Bourbon
▪️.75oz Italian Sweet Vermouth 
▪️.5oz Biscotti Liqueur 
▪️Bar-spoon of Salted Caramel Syrup 
▪️4 dashes of Fig & Fennel Bitters
Glass: Double Old Fashioned
Garnish: Painted Edible 24k Gold (What!?), Cherry & Orange Peel

Mind Blown…I am absolutely nerding out right now! 🤓🤯
I have never seen or heard of this before…just another example of why we started LTD! ⚡️

Usually we are talking about chilling the cocktail in the mixing glass but in this case HEAT is introduced first…not just heat but 800’C [1571F] 👀🔥 I am going to allow the cocktail creator to explain what we are watching:

From @agprabs at @penicillin_bar 🙌
“The campfire copper rod with the 800’C [1571F] cocktail Caramelizer…A flash of heat from the caramelizer reacts with the sugars in the cocktail, creating a richer and smoother taste. Burnt slightly down the alcohol and we wanted to achieve the metallic flavour in our cocktail 
The rod and tip are design from high quality coper for a weather resistant, and food grade safe.”

Cocktail name:
*THIS CHANGES EVERYTHING*
Leftover Basmati Rice Whiskies, Spent Coffee Amaro, Beet-Mezcal
Category: metal
Garnish: lime kafir zest 

🎥: @jonbunoan 
Leftover basmati rice by @penicillin_bar kitchen
Spent Coffee by @bar_coffee_dessert 

#mindblown #bartender #cocktails #science #recipe #mezcal #hongkong #coffee #amaro

A delicious cocktail that you can recreate at home by @spiritandspoon designed for @weissdistillingco as a tropical old fashioned riff. 🥃 It features a coconut and pineapple infused rum…recipe and instructions below! 💯

RUMMIN’ DOWN A DREAM 
2 oz @weissdistillingco 🥥🍍 Infused Rum
1/4 oz Cinnamon Syrup
2 Dashes Grapefruit Bitters 
Grapefruit Twist

“For infusion(s): Add aged rum into a mason jar, then take a healthy scoop or 2 of organic coconut oil. Give it a healthy shake then put it in the freezer for about 24 hours. The coconut oil will freeze, sometimes like a puck right at the top. Gently remove it and then fine strain the liquid. 

With Pineapple, I like to add fresh cut 🍍into long spheres and add into mason jar with the strained 🥥 rum. I let sit for about 2 days while refrigerated. I then do another fine strain.”

🎥: @calebjoyefilm 👍

#rum #infusion #tropical #oldfashioned #pineapple #coconut #coconutoil

Just imagine for a moment sitting down at a fireplace in a bottle shop full of the best liquor in the world and then watching as it spins you around and you are now sitting across the bar from @tony.roehr and he makes you the “Bidi Bidi Bom Bom” featuring @Teremana Tequila 🤯 Enjoy a  glimpse into the @raisedbywolvesspirits  experience…💯

By the way…that freezer cam was 🔥 🙌

Bidi Bidi Bom Bom
1.5oz @Teremana Tequila Blanco
.75oz lemon 
.5oz simple syrup
1oz Aperol 
2 dashes of firewater bitters
1 muddled strawberry 
Tajin rim

@therock
